Apex Villain Sheet: Gaelen the Root-Twister
High Concept: The Nymic Surgeon, The Gardener of the Dawn
Race: Wood Elf (Bosmer) — Reconstructed
Standing Stone: The Apprentice (The Conduit of Aetherius)
Power Level: Master Villain (Base "Ascended Immortal" + 8 AP)
"You cling to your 'Nature' like a child clinging to a rotting corpse. Do you not see? The Green Pact is a treaty of surrender. Y'ffre told us to keep our shape, to remain static, to rot in the prison of the Earthbones. But Dagon... Dagon offers the knife that cuts the bonds. I do not destroy the forest; I liberate it from the tyranny of physics."

Appearance: The Ascended Flesh
Gaelen is a walking violation of the Green Pact, a living testament to the mutability of reality. He was once a Bosmer, but he has used the razor-logic of the Mythic Dawn to edit his own existence.
He does not wear armor. His skin has been transmuted into a shifting, crimson chitin—a living version of the Mythic Dawn Armor spell, permanently fused to his protonymic (his true name). This carapace glows with the inner light of Mankar Camoran’s Paradise, pulsing with a heartbeat that is too fast to be mortal.
His features are elongated, severe, and beautiful in a terrifying way, mimicking the Ayleid ancestors he believes he is restoring. But the cost of his surgery is visible: his left arm is a Daedric Graft. It is not flesh, but a twisted mass of charred Spriggan heartwood and Daedric obsidian, fused to his shoulder with glowing runes. It twitches with a mind of its own, constantly clenching and unclenching, eager to reshape the world.
He smells of ozone, hot metal, and the cloying, tropical perfume of flowers that do not exist on Nirn.

